Spoof HID VendorID/ProductID as Logitech G27 (046D:C29B).

This only changes the VID/PID surfaced to userland via HID_DEVICE_ATTRIBUTES
(driver/sys/hid.c reads VENDOR_N_ID / PRODUCT_N_ID directly). The bus-level
HardwareIds in vjoy.inx (root\VID_1234&PID_BEAD&REV_0222) are deliberately
left alone — they are only used by PnP to bind the driver to the
root-enumerated bus device, never seen by games.

The HID report descriptor is still vJoy's generic gamepad layout, so any
game that inspects usage pages (steering wheel, accelerator, brake, clutch)
will still reject the device. This patch is a smoke test to find out which
games key on VID/PID alone vs. inspecting the descriptor.

Spoofing a real vendor's IDs is fine for personal testing on your own
machine. Do not redistribute.

diff --git a/inc/public.h b/inc/public.h
--- a/inc/public.h
+++ b/inc/public.h
@@ -107,11 +107,11 @@
 
 // Device Attributes
 // Vendor ID
-#define VENDOR_N_ID		0x1234
+#define VENDOR_N_ID		0x046D
 // Product ID changes if FFB is enabled or not (so we will have 2 different products and drivers)
 #ifdef VJOY_HAS_FFB
 // Product ID: FFB with registry keys in INF file
-#define	PRODUCT_N_ID	0xBEAD
+#define	PRODUCT_N_ID	0xC29B
 // Product ID: FFB without registry keys in INF file
 //#define	PRODUCT_N_ID	0x1FFB
 #else
